Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.base

Class SelectQuery

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.QueryAdaptor
au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.base.SelectQuery
All Implemented Interfaces:
Queryable
public class SelectQuery extends QueryAdaptor

A query to select items based on multiplicities. It is a powerful way to filter the results of SequenceQuery.get(...).

Type of input to submit()
Collection<Object>
Type of result
Collection<Object>, possibly empty (depending on the filter Query attached with method query(...)).
Object or null
Fails if
  1. one of the objects of the input collection does not satisfy the query set with query(Queryable) and exclusive = true (as set with exclusive())
  2. the number of objects that satisfy the query set with query(Queryable) is not within the multiplicity range (as set with multiplicity(Multiplicity))
Author:
Shayne Flint - 28/3/2012
See Also:
CoreQueries.selectOne(), CoreQueries.selectOne(Queryable), CoreQueries.selectZeroOrOne(), CoreQueries.selectZeroOrOne(Queryable), CoreQueries.selectZeroOrMany(), CoreQueries.selectZeroOrMany(Queryable), CoreQueries.selectOneOrMany(), CoreQueries.selectOneOrMany(Queryable)
